      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation with GCI < 5% on hemolysis index at all five operating points; three systematically refined mesh levels required.",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence study performed on three mesh levels (4M, 12M, 36M cells). GCI on hemolysis index ranges 4.1–8.7% across operating points; two points exceed the 5% threshold. Achieved Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented with measurement uncertainty for all five validation points.",
      "rationale": "Flow rate and rotational speed are well-documented. Fluid temperature variation during experiments is reported only as a nominal range; hematocrit lot-to-lot variability is unquantified. Achieved Gradation 2."
