      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E_rel < 20%) with experimental uncertainty bands; comparison at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error 18.4% across five points with experimental uncertainty overlapping predictions at three of five points. Two high-flow points show systematic over-prediction outside uncertainty bands. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) directly mapped to the clinical threshold; no surrogate quantities accepted at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and maps directly to the clinical threshold. Scalar hemolysis transport uses the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law; model form uncertainty in the exponent coefficients is acknowledged in the UQ report but the screening sensitivity study cited therein has not been formally linked as a structured analysis record. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
