      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by one independent analyst; post-processing scripts for hemolysis integration were not independently verified. One operating point boundary condition error was caught in review; corrections applied. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of turbulence model, hemolysis constitutive law, and RBC damage accumulation model with comparison to alternative model forms; model form uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected without comparison to LES or RSM alternatives. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis law used; Arora or Bludszuweit alternatives not evaluated. Model form uncertainty is verbally acknowledged in the UQ report alongside the screening sensitivity study, but neither is captured as a linked structured record. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain input parameters characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed; dominant inputs identified and their distributions validated against literature or measurement.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed over 12 uncertain inputs using Latin hypercube sampling (N=500 runs). Input distributions assigned from literature for viscosity, density, and power-law coefficients. The UQ report narrative references a screening sensitivity study that identified wall shear stress exposure time and the hemolysis exponent as the two most influential inputs, but this screening analysis was not encoded as a linked structured sensitivity analysis record in the credibility package. Dominant driver characterisation therefore remains unverified at the package level. Gradation 3 achieved.",
