  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-cou2-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the package with conditions. Monte Carlo UQ has been performed and declared, providing quantitative uncertainty bounds on the hemolysis index predictions across all five operating points. Achieved credibility levels fall below required levels for six of thirteen factors, most critically Model Form (2 vs. 5 required) and Test Samples (2 vs. 4 required). Acceptance is conditional on resolution of the six gap factors prior to regulatory submission. The UQ report narrative references a screening sensitivity study identifying wall shear stress exposure time and the hemolysis power-law exponent as dominant inputs; however, this study has not been linked as a structured sensitivity analysis record, and the assessment team notes this gap should be remediated in the next package revision to formally characterise dominant input drivers.",
